OL,3,CRegulator Ofcom urges tech firms to
OL,4,C'step up' to protect women and girls
OL,5,Conline
OL,7,FTechnology firms are being urged to
OL,8,F"step up" in their efforts to tackle
OL,9,Ftrolling and toxic online abuse of
OL,10,Fwomen in new guidance published by the
OL,11,Finternet and communications watchdog.
OL,13,FOfcom said women in sport, politics
OL,14,Fand other public arenas are facing
OL,15,F"significant and widespread abuse
OL,16,Fonline every day."
