OL,3,CRegulator Ofcom urges tech firms to
OL,4,C'step up' to protect women and girls
OL,5,Conline
OL,7,FEarlier this year, Sport England
OL,8,Fchairman Chris Boardman wrote to Ofcom
OL,9,Fto raise concerns over the online
OL,10,Fabuse directed against the England
OL,11,FWomen's team during Euro 2025.
OL,13,FMeanwhile, Parliament's youngest
OL,14,Ffemale MP Rosie Wrighting has
OL,15,Fpreviously spoken of several insults
OL,16,Fdirected at her, such as "Barbie" and
OL,17,F"stupid girl," saying there have been
OL,18,F"many great women" who have not gone
OL,19,Finto politics because of online abuse
OL,20,Fand safety concerns.
