OL,3,CRegulator Ofcom urges tech firms to
OL,4,C'step up' to protect women and girls
OL,5,Conline
OL,7,FThe guidance, which Ofcom said goes
OL,8,Fbeyond legal duties under the Online
OL,9,FSafety Act, includes encouraging firms
OL,10,Fto bring in prompts asking users to
OL,11,Freconsider before posting harmful
OL,12,Fcontent; imposing "timeouts" for users
OL,13,Fwho repeatedly target victims;
OL,14,Flimiting the number of comments or
OL,15,Fposts a person can make on one account
OL,16,Fto help prevent mass posting of abuse
OL,17,Fin so-called pile-ons; and allowing
OL,18,Fusers to quickly block or mute
OL,19,Fmultiple accounts at once.
