OL,3,CRegulator Ofcom urges tech firms to
OL,4,C'step up' to protect women and girls
OL,5,Conline
OL,7,FIt also recommends introducing more
OL,8,Fsophisticated tools for users to make
OL,9,Fit easier for victims to report abuse
OL,10,Fas well as simplifying the ability to
OL,11,Fset accounts to private.
OL,13,FAnother recommendation is for firms to
OL,14,Fuse automated technology known as
OL,15,F"hash-matching" to detect and remove
OL,16,Fnon-consensual intimate images.
OL,18,FBut the guidance is not enforceable,
OL,19,Fand online safety organisation
OL,20,FInternet Matters has urged the
OL,21,Fgovernment to make it mandatory.
