OL,3,CRegulator Ofcom urges tech firms to
OL,4,C'step up' to protect women and girls
OL,5,Conline
OL,7,FRachel Huggins, co-chief executive at
OL,8,FInternet Matters, said: "Too many
OL,9,Fwomen and girls experience abuse and
OL,10,Fharassment online. Ofcom's guidance
OL,11,Fincludes strong measures to make the
OL,12,Fonline world safer ` from better
OL,13,Fprivacy defaults, to changes to curb
OL,14,Fthe spread of misogynistic content `
OL,15,Fbut they are just recommendations.
OL,17,F"If government is truly committed to
OL,18,Fhalving violence against woman and
OL,19,Fgirls in a decade, they should make
OL,20,FOfcom's guidance for tech platforms a
OL,21,Fstatutory code of practice.
