OL,3,CRegulator Ofcom urges tech firms to
OL,4,C'step up' to protect women and girls
OL,5,Conline
OL,7,F"This would require platforms to
OL,8,Fimplement the measures outlined in it,
OL,9,Frather than making it a choice."
OL,11,FEchoing this, domestic abuse
OL,12,Forganisation Refuge said Ofcom's
OL,13,Fguidance "marks a welcome step towards
OL,14,Ftackling misogyny and domestic abuse
OL,15,Fin digital spaces, but meaningful
OL,16,Fprotection for women and girls will
OL,17,Frely on tech companies engaging fully
OL,18,Fwith the guidance and effectively
OL,19,Fputting it into practice."
